﻿## Summary
- preserve `stuck_recovery` through reply-run session-id fallback and embedded-run cancel plumbing so recovery no longer degrades into a fake user abort
- require stale tracked progress before active embedded/reply work is abort-drained, even when active-abort recovery is enabled
- add regressions for fresh terminal progress, fresh active reply work, and streamed model progress so long-but-active runs stay alive

## Testing
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.auto-reply-reply.config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-run-registry.test.ts`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.logging.config.ts src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.integration.test.ts`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-embedded-agent.config.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts`

## Real behavior proof
- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Verify that this patch (1) preserves `stuck_recovery` when aborting reply work via the session-id fallback and (2) skips stuck-session recovery for an active embedded run that has fresh tracked progress, instead of aborting it as if it were stale.
- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw checkout on Windows 11, Node/`pnpm exec tsx` runtime harness, against the real repo modules in this branch after commit `159943a6c0`. This was a direct runtime exercise of the shipped modules, not a Vitest mock run.
- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:
  ```powershell
  @'
  import { createReplyOperation, abortReplyRunBySessionId, testing as replyTesting } from "./src/auto-reply/reply/reply-run-registry.js";
  import { recoverStuckDiagnosticSession, testing as recoveryTesting } from "./src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.runtime.js";
  import { resetDiagnosticRunActivityForTest, markDiagnosticRunProgressForTest, getDiagnosticSessionActivitySnapshot } from "./src/logging/diagnostic-run-activity.js";
  import { setActiveEmbeddedRun, testing as runsTesting, clearActiveEmbeddedRun } from "./src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/runs.js";

  function makeHandle() {
    let abortCount = 0;
    let cancelReasons = [];
    const handle = {
      kind: "embedded",
      async queueMessage() {},
      isStreaming: () => true,
      isCompacting: () => false,
      cancel: (reason) => {
        cancelReasons.push(reason ?? "undefined");
      },
      abort: () => {
        abortCount += 1;
      },
    };
    return {
      handle,
      getAbortCount: () => abortCount,
      getCancelReasons: () => cancelReasons.slice(),
    };
  }

  replyTesting.resetReplyRunRegistry();
  runsTesting.resetActiveEmbeddedRuns();
  recoveryTesting.resetRecoveriesInFlight();
  resetDiagnosticRunActivityForTest();

  const replyOp = createReplyOperation({
    sessionKey: "agent:main:main",
    sessionId: "session-stuck-recovery",
    resetTriggered: false,
  });
  const aborted = abortReplyRunBySessionId("session-stuck-recovery", { reason: "stuck_recovery" });
  console.log("[reply-registry]");
  console.log(JSON.stringify({
    aborted,
    result: replyOp.result,
    abortSignalReason: replyOp.abortSignal.reason instanceof Error ? replyOp.abortSignal.reason.message : String(replyOp.abortSignal.reason),
  }, null, 2));

  replyTesting.resetReplyRunRegistry();
  runsTesting.resetActiveEmbeddedRuns();
  recoveryTesting.resetRecoveriesInFlight();
  resetDiagnosticRunActivityForTest();

  const active = makeHandle();
  setActiveEmbeddedRun("session-live-progress", active.handle, "agent:main:main");
  markDiagnosticRunProgressForTest({
    runId: "run-live-progress",
    sessionId: "session-live-progress",
    sessionKey: "agent:main:main",
    reason: "model chunk observed from runtime harness",
  });
  const snapshotBefore = getDiagnosticSessionActivitySnapshot({
    sessionId: "session-live-progress",
    sessionKey: "agent:main:main",
  });
  const outcome = await recoverStuckDiagnosticSession({
    sessionId: "session-live-progress",
    sessionKey: "agent:main:main",
    ageMs: 180_000,
    queueDepth: 1,
    allowActiveAbort: true,
  });
  const snapshotAfter = getDiagnosticSessionActivitySnapshot({
    sessionId: "session-live-progress",
    sessionKey: "agent:main:main",
  });
  console.log("[stuck-recovery]");
  console.log(JSON.stringify({
    snapshotBefore,
    outcome,
    abortCount: active.getAbortCount(),
    cancelReasons: active.getCancelReasons(),
    snapshotAfter,
  }, null, 2));
  clearActiveEmbeddedRun("session-live-progress", active.handle, "agent:main:main");
  '@ | pnpm exec tsx -
  ```
- **Evidence after fix**:
  ```text
  [reply-registry]
  {
    "aborted": true,
    "result": {
      "kind": "aborted",
      "code": "aborted_by_system",
      "reason": "stuck_recovery"
    },
    "abortSignalReason": "Reply operation aborted by system reason=stuck_recovery"
  }
  [stuck-recovery]
  {
    "snapshotBefore": {
      "activeWorkKind": "embedded_run",
      "hasActiveEmbeddedRun": true,
      "lastProgressAgeMs": 1,
      "lastProgressReason": "model chunk observed from runtime harness"
    },
    "outcome": {
      "status": "skipped",
      "action": "observe_only",
      "reason": "active_embedded_run",
      "sessionId": "session-live-progress",
      "sessionKey": "agent:main:main",
      "activeSessionId": "session-live-progress",
      "activeWorkKind": "embedded_run"
    },
    "abortCount": 0,
    "cancelReasons": [],
    "snapshotAfter": {
      "activeWorkKind": "embedded_run",
      "hasActiveEmbeddedRun": true,
      "lastProgressAgeMs": 84,
      "lastProgressReason": "model chunk observed from runtime harness"
    }
  }
  [diagnostic] stuck session recovery skipped: sessionId=session-live-progress sessionKey=agent:main:main age=180s queueDepth=1 activeSessionId=session-live-progress
  [diagnostic] stuck session recovery outcome: status=skipped action=observe_only sessionId=session-live-progress sessionKey=agent:main:main activeSessionId=session-live-progress activeWorkKind=embedded_run reason=active_embedded_run
  ```
- **Observed result after fix**: The session-id fallback now preserves `reason: "stuck_recovery"` all the way into the reply operation result and abort signal. In the live-progress recovery case, the real runtime returns `status: "skipped"`, keeps the embedded run active, and does not call `abort()` or `cancel()` on the active handle.
- **What was not tested**: I did not rerun a multi-minute end-to-end Feishu + `claude-cli` channel repro in this environment, and I did not capture UI/video proof from a live chat surface.

## Notes
- `diagnostics.stuckSessionWarnMs` / `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs` and the default `warnMs x 3` / minimum 5 minute behavior are already documented in the current docs/config help, so this PR focuses on the runtime regressions from `#88870`.

Closes #88870
